\title{Metric Space}
\date{2026-03-10}
\author{boat}
\taxon{Definition}
\import{math-lib}

\p{
A \strong{metric space} is an ordered pair #{(M,d)} where #{M} is a set and #{d} is a \strong{metric} on #{M}, i.e., a function #{d:M\times M \to \rr} satisfying the following axioms for all points #{x,y,z \in M}:
}

\ul{
\li{#{d(x,x) = 0}}
\li{#{\text{If } x\neq y,\text{ then } d(x,y)>0}. (Positivity)}
\li{#{d(x,y) = d(y,x)}. (Symmetry)}
\li{#{d(x,z) \leq d(x,y) + d(y,z)}. (Triangle inequality)}
}

